summary: Completed comprehensive testing of Etho Parts auto store application. Backend APIs are 93% functional with excellent authentication, product management, and order processing. Frontend UI is fully functional with Ethiopian branding, responsive design, and complete e-commerce flow. One minor backend API issue identified.

flaky_endpoints.issue: Returns 520 server error when buyer tries to fetch their orders
flaky_endpoints.impact: Buyers cannot view their order history in dashboard

integration_issues.issue: Shows 'Failed to load data' error message despite stats API working

issues: Minor accessibility warnings for DialogContent components missing descriptions

passed_tests: Homepage loads with Ethiopian flag stripe and Etho Parts branding
Navigation links functional (Home, Categories, Products, About, Track Order)
Categories section displays 8 categories with proper filtering
Products section shows auto parts with images and details
User authentication (admin, seller login and buyer registration)
Admin dashboard accessible with role-based access control
Seller dashboard functional with product management
Shopping cart opens and displays items correctly
Order tracking page loads and form is functional
Responsive design works on mobile devices
Backend APIs: authentication, product CRUD, order creation, payment verification
Admin and seller stats endpoints working

success_percentage.frontend: 95% (All major features working, minor UI error message)

action_item_for_main_agent: Fix the buyer orders endpoint (GET /api/orders) that returns 520 error when buyers try to fetch their order history. This prevents buyers from viewing orders in their dashboard. Also investigate the admin dashboard 'Failed to load data' error message.
